SPECIAL  
BROADCAST
November 1,  2001
10:30-noon ET, 9:30-11 a.m. CT, 8:30-10  a.m. MT
A Heightened Look at our System....Now That We Know What the "New Normal" is,  We Have Work To Do" 
September 11 changed the  world! 
Do you remember where you were when you first heard about  the tragic events that occurred in New York City and Washington, DC??
A  special task force met on September 27 to discuss how best to communicate and  educate what September 11 means to our daily business lives.   Representatives from El Paso Corp., ONEOK, Inc., Reliant Energy, TXU,  Dominion Energy, Iroquois Pipeline, Williams Gas Pipeline, Columbia Gas,  Columbia Gulf Transmission and Alliance Pipeline created a preliminary outline  for a Special CTN Broadcast.  David Jones, Tennessee Gas Pipeline VP  Operations and Earl Fischer, Atmos Energy Senior VP will lead the task force  efforts.
Mike McGonagill, Alliance Pipeline General Manager-US Operations  will serve as the program host.  Speakers have been invited from the FBI,  security consultants, energy security officers, industry leaders, Department of  Energy and FERC representatives. 
Three separate panels will discuss  regulatory agency response and expectations regarding system security and what companies can  and are doing to protect:
?       Physical Assets 
?       Human Assets 
